<p>On the podcast, the TV star revealed she had recently suffered what she thought was a devastating setback, when she thought she'd taken her hormonal medication at the wrong time. </p>

<p>She said: 'I just cried all night long. I was filled with complete fear and dread and thought I had put everything in jeopardy after all we had been through. I have never beaten myself up so much'.   </p>

<p>Luckily, the former TV host quickly learned she'd taken the medicine at the right time.   </p>

<p>Fiona recently revealed her 'traumatic' and 'lonely' journey in an interview with The Daily Telegraph. </p>

